									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>A beautiful meditation on the nature of religion, the difference between aspiring and demanding. I love the imagery: &#8220;cream into butter&#8221;, &#8220;sprouting of the corn&#8221;. I like the mystery of the white ships clarifying into religious promises as the story progresses. </p>
<p>Small niggles: I did not like the &#8220;flung&#8221; at the start, it seemed the wrong way to use it. I also was slightly jarred by &#8220;our people&#8221; &#8211; unless I am missing something? Is the central pair the king and queen or something of this sort? A bit strange to me.</p>
<p>I loved the final paragraph, the defiance of &#8220;I hope they do not come.&#8221;</p>
<p>Thank you!</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

